.TH "gmap_read_table" 9 "gmap_read_table" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gmap_read_table \- get an unsigned long value from a guest page table using absolute addressing, without marking the page referenced.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gmap_read_table
.BI "(struct gmap *gmap "  ","
.BI "unsigned long gaddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gmap" 12
pointer to guest mapping meta data structure
.IP "gaddr" 12
virtual address in the guest address space
.IP "val" 12
pointer to the unsigned long value to return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if the value was read, -ENOMEM if out of memory and -EFAULT
if reading using the virtual address failed. -EINVAL if called on a gmap
shadow.

Called with gmap->mm->mmap_lock in read.
